race.comment: CHIEF WITNESS (6) had no luck at all at Doomben but was tracking well into that. He's going to have to do it the hard way but will present at peak fitness and should go close. Expect a much sharper effort from the Gollan-trained VORACIOUS (10), following two disappointing runs this preparation. He's won a Doomben trial since the Gold Coast outing 32 days ago and Maloney sticking aboard is a positive. May sit more forward today and he'd be right in the finish at best. TYPHOON TIP (13) turned the form around beaten 1.5L here in stronger grade and it was a big effort after settling rearward. She has an inside gate and keeps the handy 3kg claim. Will present fitter again and has each way claims holding the form. CAPTAIN FENKEL (1) resumes and was last seen narrowly beaten at Eagle Farm over 1850m in much stronger. He's won at this trip and first-up and has a handy 3kg claim. Can't be taken lightly.
